<item>
            <title>[METAMODEL-95] Salesforce - Query for column of type double always return value 1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/METAMODEL-95</link>
                <project id="12314523" key="METAMODEL">Apache MetaModel (Retired)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I performed a query for a table, which contains columns of type double.&lt;br/&gt;
The result for these columns was always 1, regardless of the actual value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I verified the actual value by using Salesforce developer console.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I tracked the bug to SalesforceDataSet:111&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            if (columnType.isNumber()) &lt;/p&gt;
{
                return NumberComparator.toNumber(columnType.isNumber());
            }

&lt;p&gt;should be:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            if (columnType.isNumber()) &lt;/p&gt;
{
                return NumberComparator.toNumber(value);
            }

&lt;p&gt;Another option for a fix is to use the ColumnType.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
